0131.Decorum does one dignity More than life guard its purity.
0132.Virtues of conduct all excel; The soul aid should be guarded well.
0133.Good conduct shows good family Low manners mark anomaly.
0134.Readers recall forgotten lore, But conduct lost returns no more.
0135.The envious prosper but ill The ill-behaved sinks lower still.
0136.The firm from virtue falter not They know the ills of evil thought.
0137.Conduct good ennobles man, Bad conduct entails disgrace mean.
0138.Good conduct sows seeds of blessings Bad conduct endless evil brings.
0139.Foul words will never fall from lips Of righteous men even by slips.
0140.Though read much they are ignorant Whose life is not world-accordant.
